                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#135v" facs="138">Fol. 135v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1015Flagellation">Flagellation of Jesus</ref> with caption <q>“Barrabas,” “The scourging of Jesus Christ,” “Jews”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#136r" facs="138">Fol. 136r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1093TakingRobeofJesus">Taking off the Robe of Jesus</ref> with caption <q>“Jews,” “The stripping of the robe of Our Lord, Jesus Christ,” “Jews” </q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#136v" facs="139">Fol. 136v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> with caption (crude drawing in pencil)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d10">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #6v #13r #20r #29r #36r #41v #50r #60r #67v #72v #83r #93r #95v #101r #106v #117v" facs="003 009 015 022 031 038 044 052 062 070 075 085 095 098 103 109 120">folss. 1r, 6v, 13r, 20r, 29r, 36r, 41v, 50r, 60r, 67v, 72v, 83r, 93r, 95v, 101r, 106v, 117v, </locus> (elaborate haräg);
                      a line of alternating red and black dots serves as a divider between psalms and sections (e.g., <locus target="#1r #1v" facs="003 004">1r, 1v, </locus>);
                      <locus target="#7r #93r #95v" facs="009 095 098">7r, 93r, 95v, </locus> (multiple full stops connected by red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#41r #49v #59v #67r #72r #82v #106r #117r #123r #131r" facs="043 052 062 069 074 085 108 119 125 133">41r, 49v, 59v, 67r, 72r, 82v, 106r, 117r, 123r, 131r</locus> (line of full stops between lines of alternating red and black dots).
